Rating: 3
This is a new grilling staple in our house. We've tried it with skin-on thighs and breasts also, and find that the thighs are best. They do take some tending on the grill but are well worth it. The marinade is easy to put together, but don't be tempted to use dried oregano - the fresh herb is part of the charm of this recipe.

Rating: 3
Easy & tasty. Got thumbs up from both the adults & the young kids. We used bone-in legs & thighs, took the skins off (so the meat would really absorb the marinade) & marinated them for about 4 hours before grilling them. We all liked the garlicky-lemony flavor. The next day, everyone agreed the leftovers made for a good lunch. Now, I'm making them again for a dinner with guests for tomorrow night, and this time am marinating them overnight to see if that makes a difference. Will definitely keep this on our easy-dinner & good-for-guests recipe list.

