Rating: 3
I rated this a 7.5 out of 10, and followed the recipe exactly, marinating for about 10 hours. It was good but not spectacular. It was a refreshing change from the spicy dry rubs we usually use, and had a nice clean, fresh flavour which was nice on a hot summer day. I'd do this again, and wouldn't limit myself to legs. I would use pieces that were the same size to aid in the grilling. It did take about 30 minutes of near constant attention over the grill.

